parameters: --! Aomaru! I won't let you escape!

I've defeated all your underlings. It's time for you to pay
your dues, isn't it?

Hmph. Seems those skeletons were useless, eh? You call me
the enemy of those courtesans, but you're the enemy of my
sister Iyegiku as well. I'll kill you with my own hands
right here.

Momiji, I will personally torment you. I'm free now. It
doesn't matter if you're the daughter of the head of the
family!

Huh? What, you don't know? The war demons are comrades from
the same village. It's a story from over a hundred years
ago. Momiji and I are the end result of humans turned into
demons--
Karin-chan! It's dangerous to get close! Step back!

Your name was O-Ri in the pleasure district, but it's Karin,
huh? Ah, I see. So you're Chutarou-san's daughter... Indeed,
there's a resemblance. Your face is just like Korin-san's.

--! That's right! Why do you even know about it?! I don't
know anything about my father and mother's past! Tell me
everything!

That's my line! How is it that you, who should not be a
demon, are still alive in this era? You were just a baby
over a hundred years ago!

A baby...? I don't know anything about that either!? Just
tell me everything you know about my father and mother!

Heh! I don't like the idea of telling my sister's enemy for
free. If you can beat me, then maybe I'll tell you. But
that's a big if! Gehahaha--!
--! Uwaaah, it's hot! The flames again...!

Here it comes! Karin-chan, get ready with your sword! Flames
won't work on Aomaru. Be careful!
Got it! Momiji-san, please cover me! I'll attack Aomaru!

Karin. I don't know why you're still alive as a human, but
I'll burn everything to ashes! Take this, Aomaru-sama's
Flame Strike Dance--!!
--Gahaah! Damn it...! She broke through my flame strike!

This is the end for you, Aomaru! Feel the resentment of the
courtesans you killed! Yaaah--!!
Guu... Ah...! Damn it! This little girl...!

We've won... Now, keep your promise. Can you tell us the
name of the village where you lived?
Heh... Why don't you ask Momiji? Tell her... right...?

Karin-chan... When you came to visit my mansion last time, I
failed to tell you until the end... The name of the village
where our clan lived--it is--

Yes. We lived deep in the mountains east of Mount Fuji's
base. However, during the Warring States period, we were
attacked by an army from the west... We were destroyed
against our will... leaving nothing but ruins...

Out of 300 villagers, only 6 were supposed to have
survived... but there was one more survivor, and that's you,
Karin--

Eh? Me too...!? But that was over a hundred years ago,
right?

Yes, that's why I'm also confused. How did Chutarou-san,
Korin-san, and you, Karin-chan survive for over a hundred
years without becoming demons...

Kokuyou Tengu: "Us demons have prolonged our lives by
consuming humans. You're not a demon, are you? Or are you
actually a demon who, like Momiji, secretly feasted on human
corpses? Kekeke!"

Masaki: "To continue living as a demon, you killed and ate
the courtesans you kidnapped from the pleasure quarters,
didn't you? I saw many pitiful corpses of courtesans on my
way here."

Kokuyou Tengu: "That's right. They were the ones I killed
and ate. The flesh of young girls is rich in nutrients and
was the best. Gehahaha!"

Karin: "Even after I learned to wield a sword, I intended
not to kill living beings, but you are not human but a
demon... I will avenge the courtesans. The resentment of
those who were killed unjustly--I will clear it!"

Kokuyou Tengu: "Gehahaha--! Annoying as it is, you're a
dignified woman! That baby has truly become a fine woman...
If I'm to be killed by the daughter of the respected
Chutarou-san, I can't complain. Let me sleep by your
sword...ze..."

Momiji: "What's with that look of pity in your eyes when you
look at me, Momiji."

Kokuyou Tengu: "I've always cared about you, my childhood
friend... See ya... Live long... if you can... I'm going to
meet my sister... ahead of you..."

Karin: "...I'm sorry, Momiji-san. I... with my own hands...
took down your childhood friend..."

Momiji: "No... It was his fate to live on as a demon.
There's no need for you to apologize, Karin-chan."

Momiji: "When Fuma no Sato fell to ruin, we ate the flesh of
demons by the order of our clan head. That was our original
sin--becoming demons and surviving by annihilating the enemy
forces with inhuman strength. Since then, we war demons had
no choice but to live by consuming humans."

Momiji: "Killing people to eat them... I couldn't do it...
The reason I lived in the pleasure quarters for so long was
because there was no shortage of dead bodies. Courtesans who
died from illness, unattended by temples, not even
cremated—I took care of their bodies..."

Momiji: "The graves along the way... they are evidence of my
sins... To continue living... I consumed the flesh of the
dead..."

Karin: "You don't have to say anything more, Momiji-san.
Please don't look so sad... okay? You're not a demon. You're
a kind person who can shed tears for the dead..."
Hou-Chiku: "Hohoho! Well, well... Aomaru has died, has he?"

Hou-Chiku: "My name is Hou-Chiku. One of the war demons. You
lot are obstacles to us—I shall take you down here."

Hou-Chiku: "Did you think I could only attack with threads?
I can also manipulate armor. Now, my puppets, kill the
traitors of Fuma!"

Hou-Chiku: "Hohoho! Indeed, what splendid skill♪ Yegiku,
Magara, Aomaru—there's a reason you could defeat three of
Fuma's war demons."

Karin: "If you intend to fight as well, I won't hold back!
Come down from there!"

Karin-chan, fighting back-to-back battles is
disadvantageous! We should retreat for now...!

Hou-Chiku: "You think that's all the puppets I brought?
You're mistaken."

Hou-Chiku: "Hoho! I won't let you escape. This ruin will be
your graveyard! You'll be buried alongside Aomaru's corpse!"

"My wounds have finally healed. I heard you were headed to
this pleasure quarter ruin and hurried over!"

"Nuu... You're destroying the puppets I crafted with such
love!"

"You're the only one left, old war demon--! Present your
shriveled head for us to take!"
"--Nuuu!? To think you'd use dual swords, how vexing!"

"Don't underestimate an Iga ninja! This will be the end for
you!"

"Hmph, my main duty is as a scout. An old man like me will
take his leave here. I must report back to the lord."

"Indeed. I value honor, but surviving is more important than
dying in battle. You, as a ninja, should understand, right?
There will be another chance to fight soon enough. Farewell
then. Hohoho!"

Phew... It seems we've somehow managed to survive this time
as well.
Thank you for your help, Yugiri-san.

Momiji-dono. I apologize for attacking you when we first
met. You've saved me twice now. This should repay some of my
debt to you.

Thank you so much, Yugiri-chan. I talked big, but honestly,
I was already at my limit...

The enemy we faced at the bandit fortress was the Flame War
Demon, wasn't it? Are we going to leave his corpse here as
it is?

No, I will make a grave for him. We fought as enemies, but
he was a childhood friend from the same town... and for the
courtesans who were abducted and killed by Aomaru.

That's right. It'll be quicker if the three of us do it
together.

Hey hey, did you come all this way just to see me? It's
tough being a popular guy! Gehaha!

--Aomaru! Just as I sensed, you were in this mansion! You'll
pay for what you've done to the courtesans! I'll take you
down right here!

Hah! There's no need for me to fight. These guys are more
your speed.

This door won't open unless you defeat all these guys. Well,
good luck. Hahaha--!
Wait, wait! Ugh, he got away!

Ugh...! Skeletons are so creepy...! I don't want to fight
anymore...

It's a hassle, but it seems we have to defeat all the
enemies in this room to chase after Aomaru. Let's take them
down.
